{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>C-Jun-amino-terminal kinase (JNK)-interacting protein 3 (JIP3) and 4 (JIP4) are two highly related scaffolding proteins for MAP kinases. They are binding partners for molecular motors kinesin-1 and dynactin, as well as for the small G protein ARF6, which they bind through their leucine zipper II (LZII) region [[cite:PUB00090295], [cite:PUB00090296], [cite:PUB00090294]]. ARF6, together with JIP3 and JIP4, regulates membrane-tethered membrane type 1-matrix metalloproteinase exocytosis in cancer invasion [[cite:PUB00090297]].</p>\n\n<p>The function of JIP4 has been shown to be different from that of other JIP proteins. Although JIP4 binds JNK, it does not activate JNK signaling [[cite:PUB00090301]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2w83", "name" "Crystal structure of the ARF6 GTPase in complex with a specific effector, JIP4"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR13886" "JNK/SAPK-ASSOCIATED PROTEIN"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "JNK-interacting protein 3/4", "short" "JIP3/JIP4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 7, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 996, "taxa" 3945, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 7853, "sets" 0, "proteins" 7853, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2824}, "pathways" 3}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR039911", :literature {"PUB00090294" {"URL" nil, "issue" "Pt 3", "authors" ["Llinas P" "Chenon M" "Nguyen TQ" "Moreira C" "de Regibus A" "Coquard A" "Ramos MJ" "Guerois R" "Fernandes PA" "Menetrey J."], "ISO_journal" "Acta Crystallogr F Struct Biol Commun", "DOI_URL" "https://doi.org/10.1107/S2053230X16001576", "medline_journal" "Acta Crystallogr F Struct Biol Commun", "title" "Structure of a truncated form of leucine zipper II of JIP3 reveals an unexpected antiparallel coiled-coil arrangement.", "year" 2